The paper presents a novel algorithm for injecting external knowledge into induction algorithms using feature generation, which is a common technique in machine learning. The application domain is text classification, which falls under natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). The use of large semantic knowledge bases suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (AI) and knowledge representation. The paper also mentions collaborative knowledge bases, which could be related to databases (DB). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.IR, and cs.DB.
